1002
00:40:17,150 --> 00:40:18,619
I'm fine.

1003
00:40:18,652 --> 00:40:20,053
I know you've been going
through a rough time.

1004
00:40:20,086 --> 00:40:21,087
We're all worried
about you.

1005
00:40:21,121 --> 00:40:22,488
I'm okay.

1006
00:40:24,991 --> 00:40:27,694
Okay.
Alright.

1007
00:40:27,728 --> 00:40:28,929
I'm taking a few days off.

1008
00:40:28,962 --> 00:40:30,463
I got a call from California.

1009
00:40:30,496 --> 00:40:31,965
Uh, my dad died.

1010
00:40:31,998 --> 00:40:34,835
‐ What? W‐w‐what happened?
‐ Nothing, I don't know.

1011
00:40:34,868 --> 00:40:36,036
Some car wreck or something.

1012
00:40:36,069 --> 00:40:38,071
They weren't real clear
on the details.

1013
00:40:38,104 --> 00:40:40,507
Um, but I got to go...

1014
00:40:40,541 --> 00:40:44,044
claim the body
and stuff like that. So..

1015
00:40:44,077 --> 00:40:45,078
I'm sorry.

1016
00:40:45,111 --> 00:40:48,549
Yeah.
I...uh, know.

1017
00:40:51,284 --> 00:40:52,986
Alright, I'll talk,
I'll talk to you later.

1018
00:40:53,019 --> 00:40:54,821
‐ 'No, no. Hey, come on in.'
‐ No, it's okay. No, no.

1019
00:40:54,855 --> 00:40:57,023
‐ I'll talk to you later.
‐ Come on in. I'll make coffee.

1020
00:40:57,057 --> 00:40:59,192
‐ Come on.
‐ Alright.

1021
00:41:02,629 --> 00:41:06,066
I looked him dead in the eye
and I said, "That might fly

1022
00:41:06,099 --> 00:41:09,169
"with your Hollywood
chippies, Mr. President.

1023
00:41:09,202 --> 00:41:10,737
But I am a lady."

1024
00:41:10,771 --> 00:41:12,238
So, what did he do?

1025
00:41:12,272 --> 00:41:14,941
He took his hand off
my rear and apologized.

1026
00:41:14,975 --> 00:41:16,242
And that was it?

1027
00:41:16,276 --> 00:41:17,678
Then I slept with him.

1028
00:41:19,546 --> 00:41:21,648
May I freshen you up?

1029
00:41:21,682 --> 00:41:23,517
No, thank you.
I have to drive.

1030
00:41:23,550 --> 00:41:24,818
And it's getting late.

1031
00:41:24,851 --> 00:41:27,220
Time for the fat lady
to sing.

1032
00:41:27,253 --> 00:41:28,889
I like you, Carol.

1033
00:41:28,922 --> 00:41:32,158
‐ You remind me of me.
‐ Thank you.

1034
00:41:32,192 --> 00:41:35,929
I think you might
just possess the..

1035
00:41:35,962 --> 00:41:40,266
...extreme bullheaded
stubbornness..

1036
00:41:40,300 --> 00:41:43,537
...to make this
clinic thing work.

1037
00:41:43,570 --> 00:41:45,906
How would you like some seed
money to start you off?

1038
00:41:48,575 --> 00:41:51,177
Seventy‐five thousand dollars?

1039
00:41:51,211 --> 00:41:53,614
Uh, you haven't even
read my proposal.

1040
00:41:55,015 --> 00:41:58,251
It's my foundation.
Just don't tell my grandson.

1041
00:41:58,284 --> 00:42:01,722
I have a stern,
unapproachable image to keep up.

1042
00:42:01,755 --> 00:42:03,123
Oh, well, as far as
I'm concerned

1043
00:42:03,156 --> 00:42:04,791
this meeting was hell
from beginning to end.

1044
00:42:04,825 --> 00:42:07,293
‐ Exactly.
‐ Thank you so much.

1045
00:42:09,062 --> 00:42:10,964
Wow.

1046
00:42:29,916 --> 00:42:32,786
Good, good. Ha‐ha.
You're not too late.

1047
00:42:32,819 --> 00:42:34,955
I wanted to get
this celebration rolling.

1048
00:42:34,988 --> 00:42:37,257
Celebration?

1049
00:42:37,290 --> 00:42:40,026
I got a supersaver ticket
to Atlanta.

1050
00:42:40,060 --> 00:42:41,895
Tommy's gonna introduce
me to some people

1051
00:42:41,928 --> 00:42:45,231
and his sister‐in‐law
is a realtor.

1052
00:42:45,265 --> 00:42:48,268
‐ So, you had a good day.
‐ No, not just me.

1053
00:42:48,301 --> 00:42:51,071
Tommy‐Tommy knows some doctors
at the County hospital.

1054
00:42:51,104 --> 00:42:53,674
Oh.
Sounds too good to be true.

1055
00:42:53,707 --> 00:42:56,309
We can make this happen.
We can make this work.

1056
00:42:59,179 --> 00:43:01,114
Hey.

1057
00:43:02,816 --> 00:43:04,751
What's wrong?

1058
00:43:08,755 --> 00:43:09,890
Hi, Kerry.

1059
00:43:09,923 --> 00:43:12,693
Ellis.

1060
00:43:12,726 --> 00:43:15,295
I know this is strange.
We‐we just met and, uh

1061
00:43:15,328 --> 00:43:17,898
here I am calling you up
to come have a drink.

1062
00:43:17,931 --> 00:43:20,166
I‐I hope you don't
misunderstand.

1063
00:43:20,200 --> 00:43:21,935
Oh, no, please.
You saved me

1064
00:43:21,968 --> 00:43:24,705
from having to watch
the local news.

1065
00:43:24,738 --> 00:43:26,206
I don't usually do
this kind of thing.

1066
00:43:26,239 --> 00:43:28,675
Sure.
That's what they all say.

1067
00:43:32,012 --> 00:43:33,814
What's on your mind?

1068
00:43:35,882 --> 00:43:39,319
I had to lay off a pretty close
friend this afternoon

1069
00:43:39,352 --> 00:43:42,155
and she didn't seem
to appreciate my suggestions

1070
00:43:42,188 --> 00:43:43,690
for getting through this.

1071
00:43:45,425 --> 00:43:47,761
She just felt fired.

1072
00:43:47,794 --> 00:43:49,696
Which is exactly
what she was.

1073
00:43:49,730 --> 00:43:51,832
That's right.

1074
00:43:51,865 --> 00:43:54,034
When you work your ass off
to try to get her job back

1075
00:43:54,067 --> 00:43:56,302
she's not gonna
appreciate that either.

1076
00:43:58,271 --> 00:44:00,741
Welcome to the wonderful
world of management.

1077
00:44:04,845 --> 00:44:08,048
Can I get you
another drink?

1078
00:44:08,081 --> 00:44:09,916
That would be great.
Thanks.

1079
00:44:15,388 --> 00:44:17,190
I wish you'd wait
and leave tomorrow.

1080
00:44:17,223 --> 00:44:19,159
Nah, I just want
to get on with it.

1081
00:44:27,868 --> 00:44:29,803
At least let me give you
a ride to the airport.

1082
00:44:29,836 --> 00:44:31,805
Nah, I'm just gonna
leave the car in parking..

1083
00:44:31,838 --> 00:44:32,906
...pick Mark up on the way.

1084
00:44:32,939 --> 00:44:35,175
I'm glad
he's going with you.

1085
00:44:35,208 --> 00:44:36,342
Yeah, it's probably
a good idea for him

1086
00:44:36,376 --> 00:44:38,278
to get out of town
for a while.

1087
00:44:44,450 --> 00:44:45,752
I'm gonna miss you.

1088
00:44:48,340 --> 00:44:49,674
I love you, Carol.

1089
00:44:59,851 --> 00:45:01,219
I love you, too.
